      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on this lite dependency parser for some medical text processing. i dont need a full transformer based one, just something that can handle these specific clinical relations for now.\n\ncan u write a python function `get_dependencies(sentence)` that returns a list of tuples `(head, child)`? \n\nhere is the exact structure i need it to hit for my current test case:\nsentence: \"patient shows signs of acute respiratory distress\"\nexpected: [(\"shows\", \"patient\"), (\"shows\", \"signs\"), (\"signs\", \"of\"), (\"of\", \"acute\"), (\"acute\", \"respiratory\"), (\"respiratory\", \"distress\")]\n\nit needs to pass this test:\ndef test_parser():\n    text = \"patient shows signs of acute respiratory distress\"\n    expected = [(\"shows\", \"patient\"), (\"shows\", \"signs\"), (\"signs\", \"of\"), (\"of\", \"acute\"), (\"acute\", \"respiratory\"), (\"respiratory\", \"distress\")]\n    assert get_dependencies(text) == expected\n    print(\"test passed!\")\n\ncan u implement it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
